<br>
What really gets my goat here is this.  There is a double standard here.  The large guilds demand a certain level of respect when they are out to kill something, yet they are unwilling to extend that to anyone else on the server.<br>
<br>
What I mean by is the following.  If one of these guilds decide to take on a mob, they expect that another guild will wait for them to finish - perhaps even outside the zone.  They expect that their camp won't be jumped if they wipe while they are still trying that mob.  These are all courtesies that they are unwilling to extend to everyone else.<br>
<br>
I remember when I was in LotD and we did CT for the first time.  AL waited for us in force outside Fear.  They didn't come in, they didn't sit in our camp, they didn't add 50 more people to the zone to add to our lag.  Maybe if we had failed, they would have come in, but I have a feeling they would have waited for us to give up.  The same with FR - we had tried Klandicar once, and they patiently waited for us outside the zone.  <br>
<br>
If DV, LotD, Relics, etc are taking down a mob, they expect to have their "space" to do it.  But when the tables are turned, they won't think twice about waiting for someone to fail 2 feet away from their camp.  They do that to each other as well, and they all bitch about it, but no one seems to stop.<br>
<br>
It boils down to courtesy.  You want to be an honorable guild, then give someone else the same courtesy you expect.  AL does it, FR does it, so we know that it's possible to be uber and still respect someone else's raid. <br>
<br>
DV should have waited outside the zone for the raid to totally fail before jumping in.  That's just my opnion.   <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=68709 > <b> <i>Kalynn Taranis</a> </B></i>
